ejiang|Taizhou]] city || {{lang|zh|\u53f0\u5dde\u5e02}} || T\u0101izh\u014du Sh\u00ec || de tseu zy\n|-\n| [[Lishui]] city || {{lang|zh-hans|\u4e3d\u6c34\u5e02}} || L\u00edshu\u01d0 Sh\u00ec || li syu zy\n|}\n\nThe eleven prefecture-level divisions of Zhejiang are subdivided into 90 [[Administrative divisions of the People's Republic of China#County level (3rd)|county-level divisions]] (36 [[District of China|district]]s, 20 [[county-level cities]], 33 [[County (People's Republic of China)|counties]], and one [[autonomous county]]). Those are in turn divided into 1,570 [[Administrative divisions of the People's Republic of China#Township level|township-level divisions]] (761 [[town of China|town]]s, 505 [[Township (Republic of China)|township]]s, 14 [[ethnic township]]s, and 290 [[subdistrict]]s).\nHengdian belongs to Jinhua, which is the largest base of shooting films and TV dramas in China. Hengdian is called \"China's Hollywood.\" At the year end of 2017, the total population is 56.57 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stats.gov.cn/tjsj/ndsj/2018/indexch.htm|title=\u4e2d\u56fd\u7edf\u8ba1\u5e74\u9274\u20142018|website=www.stats.gov.cn|access-date=28 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190106192400/http://www.stats.gov.cn/tjsj/ndsj/2018/indexch.htm|archive-date=6 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Urban areas===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" | Population by urban areas of prefecture & county cities\n|-\n!#!!City!! style=\"background:#aaf;\"|Urban area<ref name=\"2010PRCcensus\"/>!! style=\"background:#afa;\"|District area<ref name=\"2010PRCcensus\"/>!! style=\"background:#faa;\"|City proper<ref name=\"2010PRCcensus\">{{cite book |others=Compiled by \u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u4eba\u53e3\u666e\u67e5\u529e\u516c\u5ba4 [Department of Population Census of the State Council], \u56fd\u5bb6\u7edf\u8ba1\u5c40\u4eba\u53e3\u548c\u793e\u4f1a\u79d1\u6280\u7edf\u8ba1\u53f8\u7f16 [Department of Population and Social Science and Statistics, National Bureau of Statistics] |date=2012 |script-title=zh:\u4e2d\u56fd2010\u5e74\u4eba\u53e3\u666e\u67e5\u5206\u53bf\u8d44\u6599 |location=Beijing |publisher=China Statistics Print |page= |isbn=978-7-5037-6659-6 }}</ref>!!Census date\n|-\n|1||'''[[Hangzhou]]'''{{efn|name=Hangzhou|New districts established after census: [[Fuyang District|Fuyang (Fuyang CLC)]], [[Lin'an District|Lin'an (Lin'an CLC)]]. These new districts not included in the urban area & district area count of the pre-expanded city.}}||5,162,093||6,241,971||8,700,373||2010-11-01\n|- style=\"background:lightyellow;\" class=\"sortbottom\"\n|(1)||Hangzhou {{small|(new districts)}}{{efn|name=Hangzhou}}||838,452||1,284,359||{{small|''see Hangzhou''}}||2010-11-01\n|-\n|2||[[Wenzhou]]{{efn|name=Wenzhou|New district established after census: [[Dongtou District|Dongtou (Dongtou County)]]. The new district not included in the urban area & district area count of the pre-expanded city.}}||2,686,825||3,039,439||9,122,102||2010-11-01\n|- style=\"background:lightyellow;\" class=\"sortbottom\"\n|(2)||Wenzhou {{small|(new district)}}{{efn|name=Wenzhou}}||39,193||87,683||{{small|''see Wenzhou''}}||2010-11-01\n|-\n|3||[[Ningbo]]{{efn|name=Ningbo|New district established after census: [[Fenghua District|Fenghua (Fenghua CLC)]]. The new district not included in the urban area & district area count of the pre-expanded city.}}||2,583,073||3,491,597||7,605,689||2010-11-01\n|- style=\"background:lightyellow;\" class=\"sortbottom\"\n|(3)||Ningbo {{small|(new district)}}{{efn|name=Ningbo}}||239,992||491,697||{{small|''see Ningbo''}}||2010-11-01\n|-\n|4||[[Taizhou, Zhejiang|Taizhou]]||1,189,276||1,902,510||5,968,838||2010-11-01\n|-\n|5||[[Cixi, Zhejiang|Cixi]]||1,059,942||1,462,383||{{small|''see Ningbo''}}||2010-11-01\n|-\n|6||[[Rui'an]]||927,383||1,424,667||{{small|''see Wenzhou''}}||2010-11-01\n|-\n|7||[[Yiwu]]||878,903||1,234,015||{{small|''see [[Jinhua]]''}}||2010-11-01\n|-\n|8||